# Tests — {{package}}

Quick commands for this app:

```bash
# Run all app tests
php pinoox test {{package}}

# Run one file or filter
php pinoox test {{package}} --filter=AppBoot
php pinoox test {{package}} --feature

# Add a new test
php pinoox test:create ProductTest {{package}} --feature
```

## Helpers (package comes from app.php automatically)

| Helper | Example |
|--------|---------|
| `appUnderTest()` | Current package (`{{package}}`) |
| `inMyApp(fn () => …)` | Run code inside the app context |
| `myAppGet('/')` | HTTP GET against this app |
| `myAppPost('/api/x', $data)` | HTTP POST |
| `appPath(appUnderTest(), 'Controller')` | Filesystem path inside the app |

## Example feature test

```php
<?php

it('returns the home page', function () {
    $response = myAppGet('/');

    expect($response->status())->toBe(200);
});
```

## Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `../app.php` | Package name (`'package'` key) — required |
| `bootstrap.php` | Loads platform tests + reads package from app.php |
| `Pest.php` | Pest hooks (`AppTestCase`) |
| `Feature/` | HTTP / integration tests |
| `Unit/` | Pure unit tests (no HTTP) |

## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| `App package not set` | Run `php pinoox test {{package}}` (not raw pest without `--bootstrap`) |
| `app.php must define package` | Add `'package' => '{{package}}'` to app.php |
| Need an isolated fake app | Use `fakeApp('com_test_shop', ['app.php' => …])` (platform helper) |
